xplicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:448:"<p>Are you looking for the best push notifications software to keep the visitors engaged even when they’ve left your website? Push Notification is an important marketing tool that can’t be ignored by website owners anymore. It&#8217;s so useful that it&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href="https://aioseo.com/best-push-notifications-software/">7 Best Push Notifications Software (Compared)</a> first appeared on <a href="https://aioseo.com">AIOSEO</a>.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Saud Razzak";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:18168:"<p>Are you looking for the best push notifications software to keep the visitors engaged even when they’ve left your website?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Push Notification is an important marketing tool that can’t be ignored by website owners anymore. It&#8217;s so useful that it allows you to connect with your visitors after they leave your website. You can also send targeted messages to your visitors, leading to more website traffic, conversions, and sales.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this post, we’ll show you some of the best push notification software that helps you retain and engage with your visitors.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So let’s dive into the list.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What’s Push Notification and Why You Need to Use?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Push notification is the best way to keep your users engaged throughout your website. A push notification is an alert that appears on your user’s browser screen, smartphone, or any other device. The best thing is that they can be shown on the browser even when your users are not browsing your site. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>70%</strong> of people leave your site and do not come back again. With a push notification, you can encourage users to return to your site by sending a notification on a user’s desktop or mobile device.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you understand what push notification is, let’s take a look at the best push notification tools on the market.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>List of the Top Push Notification Software (2021)</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are the top <strong>7</strong> push notification tools that we’re going to check out so that you can pick the best fit for your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. <a href="https://www.pushengage.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">PushEngage</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.pushengage.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img loading="lazy" width="700" height="391" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/push-engage.png" alt="PushEngage - Best Push Notifications Software" class="wp-image-48003" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/push-engage.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/push-engage-300x168.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/push-engage-600x335.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/push-engage-107x60.png 107w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/push-engage-161x90.png 161w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://www.pushengage.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">PushEngage</a> is a powerful web push notification tool that allows you to send notifications to visitors even when they have left your website. You can bring a good percentage of these visitors back to the website with a targeted push message.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Setting up PushEngage on your website is super easy. Once correctly set up, it works on both HTTP and HTTPS versions and sends triggered messages to all browsers and devices.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can easily customize the design and style of the notification by adding custom title text, button text, images sizes, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong>:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Easy Setup:</strong> The tool can be easily set up on WordPress (<a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/pushengage/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">as a plugin</a>) and other platforms (by integrating a simple code snippet).</li><li><strong>Scheduling:</strong> You can schedule push notifications as per the visitors’ time zone.</li><li><strong>Automated Push Notifications:</strong> Send push notifications automatically at the time of your choice.</li><li><strong>Offline Notifications:</strong> Create and send offline notifications to your subscribers that they will receive when they come online.</li><li><strong>Personalization:</strong> Send personalized messages to your subscribers by adding their name, email, or any other available details.</li><li><strong>Drip Campaigns:</strong> Create sequences and drip campaigns for events and campaigns.</li><li><strong>Dynamic Segmentation:</strong> Send out better-targeted messages based on users’ actions.</li><li><strong>Cart Abandonment:</strong> Ecommerce stores can use this tool to remind shoppers about abandoned carts.</li><li><strong>Split Testing:</strong> You can run an A/B test to find the right message for better engagement.</li><li><strong>Advanced Analytics:</strong> You can easily track views, sales, and the revenue of the push notification campaigns.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The starting price of PushEngage is <strong>$9</strong> per month. There&#8217;s also a free version that comes with a lot of features.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. <a href="https://onesignal.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">OneSignal</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://onesignal.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><img loading="lazy" width="700" height="321" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/OneSignal.png" alt="OneSignal" class="wp-image-48004" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/OneSignal.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/OneSignal-300x138.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/OneSignal-600x275.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/OneSignal-131x60.png 131w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/OneSignal-196x90.png 196w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://onesignal.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">OneSignal</a> powered by superior architecture is another popular push notification tool that offers features similar to PushEngage. It&#8217;s easy to set up and allows you to send out targeted push notifications to bring the visitors back to your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While OneSignal has an amazing free plan, as your website grows, you might want to upgrade to its premium plans. Comparing to PushEngage, OneSignal&#8217;s premium plan is expensive especially when you want to increase the subscribers limit. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Ecommerce Notifications:</strong> Ecommerce message tracking helps store owners to scale store operations with upselling and cart abandoned notifications.</li><li><strong>Filter Target Audience: </strong>You can filter your audience based on user attributes such as activity and location.</li><li><strong>Split Testing:</strong> OneSignal offers split testing options for testing multiple segments and messages for controlling user behavior.</li><li><strong>Analytics and Tracking:</strong> It comes with comprehensive analytics data that lets you understand user segments and create better notifications.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The starting price of OneSignal is <strong>$9</strong> per month and offers a free lite version that doesn&#8217;t provide a lot of features.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>3. <a href="https://vwo.com/engage/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">VWO Engage</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://vwo.com/engage/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><img loading="lazy" width="700" height="344" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/VWO-Engage.png" alt="VWO Engage" class="wp-image-48005" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/VWO-Engage.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/VWO-Engage-300x147.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/VWO-Engage-600x295.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/VWO-Engage-122x60.png 122w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/VWO-Engage-183x90.png 183w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://vwo.com/engage/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">VWO Engage</a> was previously known as the PushCrew. It has been a popular choice of website owners for keeping your visitors engaged by sending push notifications.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Website owners use this tool to send push notifications that promote sales, offers, and discounts without using mobile app notifications.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One key drawback is that the segmentation tools and engagement options are quite limited.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Easy to Use:</strong>&nbsp; It&#8217;s lightweight and easy to use.</li><li><strong>Campaign Triggers:</strong> You can create campaigns with entry and exit triggers. In this scenario, the campaign starts with a user action on the site (such as subscribing to push notifications).</li><li><strong>Personalized Notifications:</strong> You can run multiple campaigns at once with the premium version of the tool. You can create personalized notifications to send to a segment of your subscribers for enhanced engagement.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing:</strong> </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The starting price is <strong>$99</strong> per month.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>4. <a href="https://www.wonderpush.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">WonderPush</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.wonderpush.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><img loading="lazy" width="700" height="400" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/WonderPush.png" alt="WonderPush" class="wp-image-48006" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/WonderPush.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/WonderPush-300x171.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/WonderPush-600x343.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/WonderPush-105x60.png 105w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/WonderPush-158x90.png 158w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://www.wonderpush.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">WonderPush</a> is a GDPR compliant web push notification tool that lets you create and send push notifications to subscribers, both on the web and mobile. In addition, you don&#8217;t need to require any programming skills to get started.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s simple to set up and offers easy tracking, automation, sequencing, and analytics. The push notification service has a 99.9% uptime and can be used for almost every niche.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, you need to pay to get all the features which includes A/B testing, personalization, unlimited staff members, unlimited notifications, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Analytics:</strong> Analyze click-through rate, open rate, subscription rate, URL clicks, and more through the om-board analytics option.</li><li><strong>Sequencing:</strong> Create sequences for your campaigns to launch and run them for maximum impact.</li><li><strong>Ecommerce Notifications:</strong> Send cart abandoned notifications, upsell, cross-sell, and offers notifications to your subscribers.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The starting price of WonderPush is <strong>€1</strong> per month.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>5. <a href="https://sendpulse.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">SendPulse</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://sendpulse.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofolow noopener"><img loading="lazy" width="700" height="326" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SendPulse.png" alt="Sendpulse" class="wp-image-48007" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SendPulse.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SendPulse-300x140.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SendPulse-600x279.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SendPulse-129x60.png 129w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SendPulse-193x90.png 193w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://sendpulse.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">SendPulse</a> is a multichannel marketing platform that combines bulk email campaigns, web push notifications, SMS, Viber, and chatbots for messengers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It also offers quick subscription options so that more visitors can opt-in to the website messages.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>SendPulse also lets you add URLs to your push notifications. This is a powerful way of promoting your products and then tracking the performance of the campaigns.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, SendPulse UI looks outdated, and some of its processes can be hard to work with and frustrating.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Auto-Scheduling:</strong> Easily schedule content that you think works best for your audience.</li><li><strong>Campaign Tracking:</strong> Create campaigns that you think fit for business and track their success on the dashboard.</li><li><strong>Monetization:</strong> Promote monetized content of advertisers with images, branding, and URL.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The starting price of SendPlus is <strong>$6.4</strong> per month. There&#8217;s a free lite version with limited features, and your subscribers will see SendPulse branding.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>6. <a href="https://www.webpushr.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">WebPushr</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.webpushr.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><img loading="lazy" width="700" height="377" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/WebPushr.png" alt="Webpushr" class="wp-image-48008" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/WebPushr.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/WebPushr-300x162.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/WebPushr-600x323.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/WebPushr-111x60.png 111w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/WebPushr-167x90.png 167w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://www.webpushr.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Webpushr</a> is a straightforward web notification tool that makes it easy to transfer your subscribers from other platforms. It offers user segmentation, automatic push notifications, sequencing multi-push, and tracking.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With Webpushr, Store owners can easily set up push notifications for abandoned cart messages, new product promos, campaigns, and events.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The major drawback is Webpushr does not offer any dial-in phone number or web chat capability.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Better Notifications:</strong> You can add action buttons, URLs, images, and even emojis to the push notifications to make them more attractive and actionable.</li><li><strong>Ecommerce Integration:</strong> It works with WooCommerce, Magento, and other eCommerce platforms.</li><li><strong>User Segmentation:</strong> Create segments based on geographical locations, browser and devices, and demographics of users.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The starting price of Webpusher is <strong>$29</strong> per month and offers a free version with limited features.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>7. <a href="https://getpushmonkey.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">PushMonkey</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://getpushmonkey.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><img loading="lazy" width="700" height="344" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/push-monkey.png" alt="Push Monkey" class="wp-image-48009" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/push-monkey.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/push-monkey-300x147.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/push-monkey-600x295.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/push-monkey-122x60.png 122w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/push-monkey-183x90.png 183w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://getpushmonkey.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">PushMonkey</a> is another good plugin that is trusted by over <strong>7500+</strong> businesses globally. It allows users to send push notifications to browsers such as Chrome, Safari, and other browsers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It works for blogs, affiliate websites, and even eCommerce stores. The push notification service offers granular filtering, segmentation, custom branding, geolocation segmentation, scheduling, easy analytics, and tracking.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One key drawback is it doesn’t offer A/B testing feature.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Scheduling:</strong> You can easily create scheduled push notifications for offline visitors.</li><li><strong>Analytics and Tracking:</strong> Track notification performance through multiple metrics.</li><li><strong>Granular Filtering:</strong> Filter data and create lists to discover what type of users interact with your notifications and create better content for notifications.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The starting price of PushMonkey is <strong>$19</strong> per month.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s all!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this post helped you to find out the best push notification software.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We recommend PushEngage push notification service because it offers great flexibility and a comprehensive feature set that helps you create and execute push notification campaigns without any hassle.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You may also want to check out our <a href="https://aioseo.com/seo-best-practices/">ultimate SEO tips to help boost your rankings</a> or learn <a href="https://aioseo.com/blog-post-seo-checklist/">how to optimize your blog post</a> and <a href="https://aioseo.com/how-to-best-optimize-images-in-wordpress/">images</a> to maximize your SEO. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>What are you waiting for? Get started with the most powerful <a href="https://aioseo.com/pricing/">WordPress AIOSEO plugin</a> today.</p>The post <a href="https://aioseo.com/best-push-notifications-software/">7 Best Push Notifications Software (Compared)</a> first appeared on <a href="https://aioseo.com">AIOSEO</a>.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:57:"https://aioseo.com/best-push-notifications-software/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:79:"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:68:"Introducing the New AIOSEO Full Site Redirects and Headline Analyzer";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:198:"https://aioseo.com/introducing-the-new-aioseo-full-site-redirect-and-headline-analyzer/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=introducing-the-new-aioseo-full-site-redirect-and-headline-analyzer";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:96:"https://aioseo.com/introducing-the-new-aioseo-full-site-redirect-and-headline-analyzer/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 27 Jul 2021 18:56:23 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Announcements";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:19:"Full Site Redirects";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17:"Headline Analyzer";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"https://aioseo.com/?p=47945";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:498:"<p>At AIOSEO, we’ve always been listening to our users&#8217; feedback to launch new features and make the user experience even better. Today, we’re pleased to announce 2 new features to level up your SEO game: Full Site Redirects, and Headline&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href="https://aioseo.com/introducing-the-new-aioseo-full-site-redirect-and-headline-analyzer/">Introducing the New AIOSEO Full Site Redirects and Headline Analyzer</a> first appeared on <a href="https://aioseo.com">AIOSEO</a>.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"Benjamin Rojas";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11172:"<p>At AIOSEO, we’ve always been listening to our users&#8217; feedback to launch new features and make the user experience even better.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Today, we’re pleased to announce <strong>2</strong> new features to level up your SEO game: <strong>Full Site Redirects</strong>, and <strong>Headline Analyzer</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With the new update, you can easily redirect your entire site and also come up with a catchy headline that boosts click-throughs on Google and drive more organic traffic.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s take a closer look…</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>1. Full Site Redirects &#8211; Overview</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Full Site Redirects feature allows you to redirect your entire website to another domain. In addition, you can also set up site aliases that you want to be redirected to the current site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With the new update, AIOSEO even lets you force URLs to be redirected from HTTP to HTTPS for improved security.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We also added the ability to add HTTP headers to the site&#8217;s responses. These can be added for the entire website <strong>OR</strong> a custom redirect.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Easily Manage Full Site Redirects</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Unlike other redirection plugins, AIOSEO gives you access to everything you need to maximize your SEO from one single plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And with our Full Site Redirects, even an absolute WordPress beginner can redirect their entire site from one domain to another.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ll now see the Full Site Redirects tab in the plugin under <strong>All in One SEO » Redirects</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="620" height="222" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-Redirect.png" alt="Redirects settings" class="wp-image-47946" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-Redirect.png 620w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-Redirect-300x107.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-Redirect-600x215.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-Redirect-168x60.png 168w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-Redirect-251x90.png 251w" sizes="(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The following options are available on this screen.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Relocate Site</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>With this option enabled, you can redirect the entire site to a new domain, except for the WordPress admin and login details. Keep in mind that when you enable this option, the site aliases and canonical settings will be disabled.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="700" height="237" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/relocate-site.png" alt="Relocate Site" class="wp-image-47947" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/relocate-site.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/relocate-site-300x102.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/relocate-site-600x203.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/relocate-site-177x60.png 177w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/relocate-site-266x90.png 266w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Site Aliases</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Site Aliases is when you want to link multiple domain names to the same website. Basically, when you control various domains, you can use an alias to keep them active while managing only one website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For instance, if you’ve two domains, https://example.com and https://example.org, and you want all traffic coming to the .org domain to be redirected towards the .com domain, you can set up site aliases to redirect the traffic.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="700" height="245" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Site-aliases.png" alt="Site Aliases" class="wp-image-47948" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Site-aliases.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Site-aliases-300x105.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Site-aliases-600x210.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Site-aliases-171x60.png 171w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Site-aliases-257x90.png 257w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Canonical Settings</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The canonical URL of a web page basically lets Google know where the original content of that page can be found in order to prevent duplicate content penalties from Google.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With the Canonical Settings option, you can redirect all URLs to a new canonical URL. For instance, you can redirect http://example.com to https://example.com, similarly you can add or remove WWW in front of the domain.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="700" height="299" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/canonical-settings.png" alt="Canonical Settings" class="wp-image-47949" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/canonical-settings.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/canonical-settings-300x128.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/canonical-settings-600x256.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/canonical-settings-140x60.png 140w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/canonical-settings-211x90.png 211w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>HTTP Headers</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>This option adds HTTP headers to the site&#8217;s responses across the site, including redirects.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, we have added two buttons that let you add predefined security and CORS headers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Cross-origin resource sharing (<em>CORS</em>) is a browser mechanism that enables controlled access to resources located outside of a given domain</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you set CORS to only load URLs from your website, https://example.com, an image that is hosted elsewhere (https://example.org) won&#8217;t be loaded on the user&#8217;s browser because of the CORS policy of the server.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The same goes for the security headers. They help prevent common security vulnerabilities like XSS attacks.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="700" height="275" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/HTTP-Header.png" alt="HTTP Header" class="wp-image-47951" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/HTTP-Header.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/HTTP-Header-300x118.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/HTTP-Header-600x236.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/HTTP-Header-153x60.png 153w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/HTTP-Header-229x90.png 229w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Read our <a href="https://aioseo.com/docs/full-site-redirects/">full site redirects documentation</a> for more details on how to redirect the entire site.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>2. Headline Analyzer &#8211; Overview</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you know 8 out of 10 people may not even read your content if the title isn&#8217;t captivating enough? To drive more traffic to your website, you need to write compelling headlines that will convince users to click the search results on Google. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The AIOSEO plugin comes bundled with a headline analyzer tool that lets you analyze&nbsp;and check if your title has the emotional value to engage your users. The best part is that you can tweak and refine the headline based on our suggestions until you find the best one for increased engagement!</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Easy Access Within Post Editor</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The SEO Headline Analyzer can be found in the post editor (Block Editor only) and lets you analyze your headline for SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you change the title of your post, the Headline Analyzer will automatically analyze it again and display the new score. It will also show a history of the previous headline that you&#8217;ve tried.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The score is based on a number of criteria that are listed below the score, such as word balance, word count, uncommon words, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="210" height="400" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/current-score.png" alt="Current Score Headline Analyzer" class="wp-image-48174" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/current-score.png 210w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/current-score-158x300.png 158w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/current-score-32x60.png 32w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/current-score-47x90.png 47w" sizes="(max-width: 210px) 100vw, 210px" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>There&#8217;s also another tab called <strong>Try New Headline</strong>, where you can test a new headline without changing the current one.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="259" height="400" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Try-New-Headline-2.png" alt="Try New Headline" class="wp-image-48176" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Try-New-Headline-2.png 259w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Try-New-Headline-2-194x300.png 194w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Try-New-Headline-2-39x60.png 39w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Try-New-Headline-2-58x90.png 58w" sizes="(max-width: 259px) 100vw, 259px" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also find the Headline Analyzer option in advanced settings. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="219" height="400" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SEO-Headline-Analyzer.png" alt="SEO Headline Analyzer" class="wp-image-48177" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SEO-Headline-Analyzer.png 219w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SEO-Headline-Analyzer-164x300.png 164w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SEO-Headline-Analyzer-33x60.png 33w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SEO-Headline-Analyzer-49x90.png 49w" sizes="(max-width: 219px) 100vw, 219px" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Read our <a href="https://aioseo.com/docs/using-the-headline-analyzer-in-all-in-one-seo/">headline analyzer documentation</a> and see how you can use this feature to create a catchy headline.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With the release of these features, we hope that our users can set up better site redirects and write great headlines that capture the interest of the readers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, thank you for your continued support in helping us make All in One SEO the&nbsp;<a href="https://aioseo.com/">best WordPress SEO plugin</a>! </p>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you haven’t done so already, click here to&nbsp;<a href="https://aioseo.com/pricing/">get started with All in One SEO today</a>!</p>The post <a href="https://aioseo.com/introducing-the-new-aioseo-full-site-redirect-and-headline-analyzer/">Introducing the New AIOSEO Full Site Redirects and Headline Analyzer</a> first appeared on <a href="https://aioseo.com">AIOSEO</a>.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:92:"https://aioseo.com/introducing-the-new-aioseo-full-site-redirect-and-headline-analyzer/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2:"13";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:79:"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:48:"What’s the Best Image Format for Your Website?";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:156:"https://aioseo.com/what-is-the-best-image-format-for-your-website/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=what-is-the-best-image-format-for-your-website";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:75:"https://aioseo.com/what-is-the-best-image-format-for-your-website/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 23 Jul 2021 12:36:34 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:19:"All in One SEO Pack";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:33:"best format for images on website";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:25:"best image format for web";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"https://aioseo.com/?p=46338";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:421:"<p>Do you want to know the best image format to use on your website? Each image format has its own characteristics so it&#8217;s important that you choose the right format based on how you want to use it. In this&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href="https://aioseo.com/what-is-the-best-image-format-for-your-website/">What’s the Best Image Format for Your Website?</a> first appeared on <a href="https://aioseo.com">AIOSEO</a>.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Saud Razzak";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5995:"<p>Do you want to know the best image format to use on your website?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Each image format has its own characteristics so it&#8217;s important that you choose the right format based on how you want to use it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this post, we&#8217;ll explain everything you need to know about choosing the best image format on your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id="3-Major-Image-Formats-That-You-Should-Use">Best 3 Major Image Formats That You Should Use</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;re the top<strong> 3</strong> common image formats that we&#8217;re going to discuss so you can choose the best one for your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Joint Photographic Experts Group (<strong>JPEG</strong>)</li><li>Portable Network Graphics (<strong>PNG</strong>)</li><li>Graphics Interchange Format (<strong>GIF</strong>)</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Alright, let&#8217;s take a look at the similarities and major differences between JPEG, PNG, and GIF.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. Joint Photographic Experts Group (JPEG)</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>JPEG is a very common image file format used by almost all websites, and the best part is that you can retain reasonable image quality even when the images are compressed to reduce the overall image file size.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>JPEG uses a&nbsp;lossy compression method&nbsp;and ensures images are as small as possible and load quickly when someone wants to view them. Even when compressed, JPEG can show millions of colors in the image.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s a quick example:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="700" height="400" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Pet.png" alt="PET JPEG" class="wp-image-46342" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Pet.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Pet-300x171.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Pet-600x343.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Pet-105x60.png 105w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Pet-158x90.png 158w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>However, JPEG isn&#8217;t preferred for screenshots and images with minimum colors because of the quality of the images.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. Portable Network Graphics (PNG)</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>PNG is another great image format that supports millions of colors. It&#8217;s best for screenshots because PNG offers much better text readability than JPEG.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can easily create banners, infographics, screenshots with clear text and images and save them in PNG format with little loss of visual quality. In fact, PNG is perfect when you have just two or three colors in the image.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The following is a screenshot of the <a href="https://aioseo.com/pricing/">AIOSEO plugin</a>. Here you can see that even when the colors are limited, the image looks good in the PNG format.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="609" height="378" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SEO-Analytics.png" alt="SEO Analysis - Best Image Format" class="wp-image-46343" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SEO-Analytics.png 609w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SEO-Analytics-300x186.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SEO-Analytics-600x372.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SEO-Analytics-97x60.png 97w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SEO-Analytics-145x90.png 145w" sizes="(max-width: 609px) 100vw, 609px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you save this image in JPEG format, there&#8217;s a high chance that the image will be blurred and the text not perfectly readable.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Best of all, PNG offers transparency that comes in handy when creating logos and icons. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>3.Graphics Interchange Format (GIF)</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>GIF is mostly used for animations and low-resolution video clips. The file size is small as it only supports up to <strong>256 </strong>colors.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="399" height="307" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/GIF.gif" alt="GIF Example" class="wp-image-46345" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This means if you’re creating a GIF with many colors, it might come out blurry. Additionally, GIFs could negatively impact the page load time as they’re often loaded after all other page assets.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id="Choose-the-Best-Image-Format">Choose the Best Image Format</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>For many websites including eCommerce stores, either JPEG or PNG is a great choice. However, the best practice is to stick to one format throughout the website to helps consistency in design. GIFs are often reserved for adding lightweight animations.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Choosing between JPEG and PNG is often a tricky decision.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>JPEG offers high compression for image data and offers much smaller image sizes with little loss of visual quality for images with lots of colors.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This makes it a great format for photographs that contain a lot of details. You’ll find JPEG at portfolio websites and eCommerce stores because of the performance boost.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On the other hand, if details within the images are important to you, PNG should be the format of choice .</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The images retain almost all details even after compression, and the file sizes are almost similar to JPEGs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this post helped you pick the best format for images on your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You may also want to check out <a href="https://aioseo.com/how-to-name-image-files-for-seo-in-wordpress/">how to name your image files for SEO in WordPress</a> and <a href="https://aioseo.com/how-to-write-alt-text-for-images-for-seo-3-easy-tips/">write Alt text for images</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not using AIOSEO yet? <a href="https://aioseo.com/pricing/">Get started with the best SEO plugin today!</a></p>The post <a href="https://aioseo.com/what-is-the-best-image-format-for-your-website/">What’s the Best Image Format for Your Website?</a> first appeared on <a href="https://aioseo.com">AIOSEO</a>.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:71:"https://aioseo.com/what-is-the-best-image-format-for-your-website/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:76:"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:48:"How to Lazy Load Images in WordPress (2 Methods)";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:136:"https://aioseo.com/how-to-lazy-load-images-in-wordpress/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-lazy-load-images-in-wordpress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:64:"https://aioseo.com/how-to-lazy-load-images-in-wordpress/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 20 Jul 2021 16:00:04 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:19:"All in One SEO Pack";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:16:"lazy load images";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"https://aioseo.com/?p=47180";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:429:"<p>Do you want to know how to lazy load images in WordPress? Enabling image lazy loading allows visitors to quickly go through your content without having to wait for the entire page to load. In this post, we&#8217;ll explain what&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href="https://aioseo.com/how-to-lazy-load-images-in-wordpress/">How to Lazy Load Images in WordPress (2 Methods)</a> first appeared on <a href="https://aioseo.com">AIOSEO</a>.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Saud Razzak";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9129:"<p>Do you want to know how to lazy load images in WordPress?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Enabling image lazy loading allows visitors to quickly go through your content without having to wait for the entire page to load. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this post, we&#8217;ll explain what lazy load images are and why you need to add them to your WordPress website.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id="What-are-Lazy-Load-images">What Are Lazy Load Images?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Lazy loading allows your website to only load images when they are visible on your user&#8217;s screen. This will increase the site performance and reduce the load time of your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Without a doubt, adding visual content is one of the best ways to boost user engagement on your site. However, adding too many images on a web page can directly impact its speed and performance.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Lazy loading of images is a solution to the performance problem because not all images are loaded on a page unless your visitors actually see them. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>With <strong>WordPress 5.5</strong>, now you can make use of image lazy loading without any further configuration. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, if you want to customize how your images lazy load, and lazy load background images, then you&#8217;ll need to use a WordPress plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id="How-to-Set-Up-Lazy-Load-Images-in-WordPress">How to Set Up Lazy Load Images in WordPress</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Now without wasting time, let&#8217;s move to the next step and learn how easy it is to set up lazy load images on WordPress using the top two methods.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Method 1: Use the WPRocket Cache Plugin</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://aioseo.com/recommends/wp-rocket/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow" title="https://aioseo.com/recommends/wp-rocket/">WPRocket</a> is the best cache plugin that speeds up your website <strong>5x</strong> faster. Although it&#8217;s a paid plugin, the features it offers are effortless.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s see how you can enable lazy load images using WPRocket.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We assumed you already set up this plugin. If not, check out our guide on how to easily set up the <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/plugins/how-to-properly-install-and-setup-wp-rocket-in-wordpress/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">WPRocket plugin on WordPress</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>All you have to do is go to the WPRocket account and navigate <strong>Media</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you can see two different options including:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Enable for Images:</strong> It can improve website loading time as images.</li><li><strong>Enable Iframes or Videos:</strong> You can also enable lazy loading for videos.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s a quick example:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="488" height="329" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/WP-Rocket-Media.png" alt="WPRocket Media Settings" class="wp-image-47186" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/WP-Rocket-Media.png 488w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/WP-Rocket-Media-300x202.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/WP-Rocket-Media-89x60.png 89w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/WP-Rocket-Media-133x90.png 133w" sizes="(max-width: 488px) 100vw, 488px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Bonus Tip:</strong> If you&#8217;re using the best hosting provider like <a href="https://aioseo.com/recommends/siteground/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">SiteGround</a>, you can use a free <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/sg-cachepress/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">SiteGround Optimizer plugin</a> with similar lazy loading features.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now let&#8217;s move to the next method.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Method 2: Set Up WordPress Lazy Loading Using Plugin</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="679" height="325" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/EWWW-Lazy-Load-Image.png" alt="Lazy Load Images Plugin" class="wp-image-47181" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/EWWW-Lazy-Load-Image.png 679w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/EWWW-Lazy-Load-Image-300x144.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/EWWW-Lazy-Load-Image-600x287.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/EWWW-Lazy-Load-Image-125x60.png 125w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/EWWW-Lazy-Load-Image-188x90.png 188w" sizes="(max-width: 679px) 100vw, 679px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Although there are a ton of plugins that offer lazy loading images, one of the best is <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/ewww-image-optimizer/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">EWWW Image Optimizer</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The EWWW image optimizer plugin is completely free and easy to use. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>First off, you&#8217;ll need to install and activate this plugin. For more details, see the detailed guide on <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/#:~:text=First%2C%20you%20need%20to%20download,reveal%20the%20plugin%20upload%20form.">how to install a WordPress plugin</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once activated, the <strong>EWWW Image Optimizer</strong> tab appears under the WordPress admin dashboard <strong>Settings</strong>. It will ask you a few things for configuration.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="621" height="394" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/EWW-Image-Optimizer-settings.png" alt="EWWW Image Optimizer Settings" class="wp-image-47182" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/EWW-Image-Optimizer-settings.png 621w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/EWW-Image-Optimizer-settings-300x190.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/EWW-Image-Optimizer-settings-600x381.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/EWW-Image-Optimizer-settings-95x60.png 95w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/EWW-Image-Optimizer-settings-142x90.png 142w" sizes="(max-width: 621px) 100vw, 621px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>On the next screen, you&#8217;ll see some recommended settings by the <strong>EWWW Plugin</strong> that you can change if necessary.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We&#8217;re focusing on <strong>Lazy Load </strong>for this tutorial, so let&#8217;s select the <strong>Lazy Load</strong> checkbox to enable it and click <strong>Save Settings</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="273" height="354" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/EWWW-Recommended-Settings.png" alt="EWWW Recommended Settings" class="wp-image-47183" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/EWWW-Recommended-Settings.png 273w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/EWWW-Recommended-Settings-231x300.png 231w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/EWWW-Recommended-Settings-46x60.png 46w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/EWWW-Recommended-Settings-69x90.png 69w" sizes="(max-width: 273px) 100vw, 273px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s all! Now your website images are automatically lazy loading and optimized.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="620" height="512" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Done-Button.png" alt="Click on the Done button" class="wp-image-47184" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Done-Button.png 620w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Done-Button-300x248.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Done-Button-600x495.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Done-Button-73x60.png 73w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Done-Button-109x90.png 109w" sizes="(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After clicking on the <strong>Done</strong> button, you&#8217;ll see the optimization score and the rest of the settings that you can change.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="581" height="397" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/EWWW-Settings.png" alt="EWWW Image Settings" class="wp-image-47185" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/EWWW-Settings.png 581w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/EWWW-Settings-300x205.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/EWWW-Settings-88x60.png 88w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/EWWW-Settings-132x90.png 132w" sizes="(max-width: 581px) 100vw, 581px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s all! We hope this post helped you understand how WordPress lazy load increases your site speed and is optimized with SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you want to learn more about SEO, please visit our<a href="https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/"> ultimate WordPress SEO guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>What are you waiting for? Get started with the most powerful <a href="https://aioseo.com/pricing/">WordPress AIOSEO plugin</a> today.</p>The post <a href="https://aioseo.com/how-to-lazy-load-images-in-wordpress/">How to Lazy Load Images in WordPress (2 Methods)</a> first appeared on <a href="https://aioseo.com">AIOSEO</a>.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:61:"https://aioseo.com/how-to-lazy-load-images-in-wordpress/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:76:"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:66:"How to Verify Your WordPress Website With Pinterest (Step by Step)";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:166:"https://aioseo.com/how-to-verify-your-wordpress-website-with-pinterest/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-verify-your-wordpress-website-with-pinterest";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:80:"https://aioseo.com/how-to-verify-your-wordpress-website-with-pinterest/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 16 Jul 2021 20:17:14 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:19:"All in One SEO Pack";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"verify website with pinterest";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"https://aioseo.com/?p=45882";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:490:"<p>Do you want to know how to verify your WordPress website with Pinterest? Pinterest is the world&#8217;s third-largest search engine after Google and YouTube. By verifying your website on Pinterest, you can drive more organic traffic from Pinterest to your&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href="https://aioseo.com/how-to-verify-your-wordpress-website-with-pinterest/">How to Verify Your WordPress Website With Pinterest (Step by Step)</a> first appeared on <a href="https://aioseo.com">AIOSEO</a>.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Saud Razzak";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17977:"<p>Do you want to know how to verify your WordPress website with Pinterest?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Pinterest is the world&#8217;s third-largest search engine after Google and YouTube. By verifying your website on Pinterest, you can drive more organic traffic from Pinterest to your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this tutorial, we’ll show you how to easily verify your website on Pinterest.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So let’s dig in.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Why Should You Verify Your Website on Pinterest?</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="700" height="400" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Verify-your-WordPress-website-with-Pinterest.jpg" alt="Verify your WordPress website with Pinterest" class="wp-image-45896" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Verify-your-WordPress-website-with-Pinterest.jpg 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Verify-your-WordPress-website-with-Pinterest-300x171.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Verify-your-WordPress-website-with-Pinterest-600x343.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Verify-your-WordPress-website-with-Pinterest-105x60.jpg 105w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Verify-your-WordPress-website-with-Pinterest-158x90.jpg 158w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Pinterest is mostly used by people who are searching for visual content to discover new ideas, inspiration or learn something new.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As many as <strong>450 million</strong> users prefer the platform to share images, GIFs, videos, and related types of visual content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If your website focuses on visual arts such as photography or an eCommerce store, Pinterest can significantly increase your web traffic and brand visibility.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>How to Easily Verify Your WordPress Site With Pinterest</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We have created this simple tutorial that covers all steps of the process. If you want to jump straight to a specific step, you can use these quick links:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href="#Upgrade-Your-Pinterest-Account-to-Business">Step 1. Upgrade Your Pinterest Account to Business</a></li><li><a href="#Claim-Your-Website-on-Pinterest">Step 2. Claim Your Website on Pinterest</a></li><li><a href="#Add-HTML-Tag-to-Your-WordPress-Website">Step 3. Add HTML Tag to Your WordPress Website</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 id="Upgrade-Your-Pinterest-Account-to-Business">Step 1. Upgrade Your Pinterest Account to Business</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>First things first, you should upgrade your personal account to a Pinterest business account.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A <a href="https://business.pinterest.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Pinterest business account</a> lets you gain access to a lot of Pinterest benefits that you wouldn’t have otherwise, including boosting brand authority, driving traffic, the ability to create and display ads, access to Pinterest insights, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Best of all, <strong>Pinterest Business</strong> is free and easy to set up.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>By default, all Pinterest account is a personal account. To claim your website on Pinterest, you&#8217;ll have to switch your personal account to a business account. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Switch From Personal to Business</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Log in to your Pinterest account, go to the top right corner, and click the dropdown arrow.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you need to click the <strong>Convert to Business</strong> link.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="620" height="285" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Convert-to-Business.png" alt="Convert to business" class="wp-image-45898" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Convert-to-Business.png 620w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Convert-to-Business-300x138.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Convert-to-Business-600x276.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Convert-to-Business-131x60.png 131w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Convert-to-Business-196x90.png 196w" sizes="(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>On the next screen, you can see all the personal and business account features, with the business account offering more features.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="306" height="285" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Click-Convert-Account-Button.png" alt="Click to the Convert account" class="wp-image-45899" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Click-Convert-Account-Button.png 306w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Click-Convert-Account-Button-300x279.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Click-Convert-Account-Button-64x60.png 64w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Click-Convert-Account-Button-97x90.png 97w" sizes="(max-width: 306px) 100vw, 306px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, click the <strong>Convert Account</strong> button. It will take you to a new screen where you need to create a business profile.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After that, add your business details such as business name, website, country, and language.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="447" height="391" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Build-your-profile.png" alt="Build your profile" class="wp-image-45900" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Build-your-profile.png 447w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Build-your-profile-300x262.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Build-your-profile-69x60.png 69w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Build-your-profile-103x90.png 103w" sizes="(max-width: 447px) 100vw, 447px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, you need to describe your business and the goals you wish to achieve with the Pinterest business account. These goals could be driving traffic to your site, generating more leads for your business, or more sales.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="349" height="276" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Describe-your-Goals-1.png" alt="Describe your goal" class="wp-image-45901" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Describe-your-Goals-1.png 349w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Describe-your-Goals-1-300x237.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Describe-your-Goals-1-76x60.png 76w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Describe-your-Goals-1-114x90.png 114w" sizes="(max-width: 349px) 100vw, 349px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>On the next screen, you need to describe who you’re (choose from blogger, store owner, influencer), and click <strong>Next</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="347" height="341" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Describe-your-business.png" alt="Describe your business" class="wp-image-45902" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Describe-your-business.png 347w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Describe-your-business-300x295.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Describe-your-business-61x60.png 61w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Describe-your-business-92x90.png 92w" sizes="(max-width: 347px) 100vw, 347px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now select <strong>Yes</strong>, if you wish to run ads on Pinterest. In our case, we’re selecting <strong>No </strong>because we don’t want to advertise at the moment. Click <strong>Next</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="547" height="352" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Running-ads-on-Pinterest.png" alt="Running ads on Pinterest" class="wp-image-45903" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Running-ads-on-Pinterest.png 547w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Running-ads-on-Pinterest-300x193.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Running-ads-on-Pinterest-93x60.png 93w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Running-ads-on-Pinterest-140x90.png 140w" sizes="(max-width: 547px) 100vw, 547px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now Pinterest will ask you where you would like to start. Here we can see <strong>3</strong> options, including sharing ideas, claiming your website, and showcasing your brand.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For this tutorial, we’re selecting <strong>Claim your Website</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="620" height="470" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Choose-Claim-your-website.png" alt="Claim your website" class="wp-image-45904" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Choose-Claim-your-website.png 620w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Choose-Claim-your-website-300x227.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Choose-Claim-your-website-600x455.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Choose-Claim-your-website-79x60.png 79w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Choose-Claim-your-website-119x90.png 119w" sizes="(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now let’s move to the next step and see how you can easily claim your WordPress website on Pinterest.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id="Claim-Your-Website-on-Pinterest">Step 2. Claim Your Website on Pinterest</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>On this screen, you can see the <strong>Claim</strong> button next to the website. It will directly take you to the claim settings page.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="620" height="328" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Select-Websites-Claims.png" alt="Select website claim" class="wp-image-45905" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Select-Websites-Claims.png 620w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Select-Websites-Claims-300x159.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Select-Websites-Claims-600x317.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Select-Websites-Claims-113x60.png 113w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Select-Websites-Claims-170x90.png 170w" sizes="(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After clicking the <strong>Claim</strong> button, Pinterest will show you a popup with the options for finalizing the claim process.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can see <strong>3</strong> methods including:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Add HTML tag — </strong>simply add an HTML code snippet to your website &lt;head&gt; section.</li><li><strong>Upload HTML file — </strong>download an HTML file and upload it to the root directory of your website.</li><li><strong>Add TXT record —</strong> add a verification record to your domain host.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="696" height="388" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Choose-how-you-want-to-claim.png" alt="Choose how you want to claim" class="wp-image-45906" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Choose-how-you-want-to-claim.png 696w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Choose-how-you-want-to-claim-300x167.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Choose-how-you-want-to-claim-600x334.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Choose-how-you-want-to-claim-108x60.png 108w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Choose-how-you-want-to-claim-161x90.png 161w" sizes="(max-width: 696px) 100vw, 696px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>While you can opt for any of the three methods, we will use the first <strong>HTML tag</strong> addition method since it is the simplest of the three options.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id="Add-HTML-Tag-to-Your-WordPress-Website">Step 3. Add HTML Tag to Your WordPress Website</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To add the HTML tag, you can install the <a href="https://aioseo.com/pricing/">All In One SEO plugin</a> on your WordPress website. For more details, see the detailed guide on <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/">how to install a WordPress plugin</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="730" height="447" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-2.png" alt="AIOSEO plugin" class="wp-image-45907" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-2.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-2-300x184.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-2-600x367.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-2-98x60.png 98w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-2-147x90.png 147w" sizes="(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’ve done with plugin installation, navigate to <strong>WordPress Dashboard » General Setting » Webmaster Tools</strong> and select the <strong>Pinterest Site Verification</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="620" height="245" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-WebMaster-Tool.png" alt="AIOSEO webmaster tools" class="wp-image-45908" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-WebMaster-Tool.png 620w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-WebMaster-Tool-300x119.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-WebMaster-Tool-600x237.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-WebMaster-Tool-152x60.png 152w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-WebMaster-Tool-228x90.png 228w" sizes="(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Once selected, the verification tab will appear on the same screen. Here you need to copy the code from Pinterest and paste it into the <strong>Pinterest Verification Code. </strong>Click <strong>Save Changes</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="620" height="269" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Pinterest-Verification-code.png" alt="Pinterest verification code" class="wp-image-45909" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Pinterest-Verification-code.png 620w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Pinterest-Verification-code-300x130.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Pinterest-Verification-code-600x260.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Pinterest-Verification-code-138x60.png 138w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Pinterest-Verification-code-207x90.png 207w" sizes="(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Go back to Pinterest and click <strong>Continue</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="620" height="345" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/click-continue-button.png" alt="Click to the continue button" class="wp-image-45910" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/click-continue-button.png 620w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/click-continue-button-300x167.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/click-continue-button-600x334.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/click-continue-button-108x60.png 108w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/click-continue-button-162x90.png 162w" sizes="(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, Pinterest asks you to verify your website by adding your site link. Once added, click <strong>Verify</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="620" height="341" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Click-Verify-Button.png" alt="Click to the Verify button" class="wp-image-45911" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Click-Verify-Button.png 620w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Click-Verify-Button-300x165.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Click-Verify-Button-600x330.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Click-Verify-Button-109x60.png 109w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Click-Verify-Button-164x90.png 164w" sizes="(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It will take a few seconds to finalize the process. Once verified, you will see the verification message.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="659" height="324" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Verification-in-Progress.png" alt="Verification in Progress" class="wp-image-45912" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Verification-in-Progress.png 659w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Verification-in-Progress-300x147.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Verification-in-Progress-600x295.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Verification-in-Progress-122x60.png 122w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Verification-in-Progress-183x90.png 183w" sizes="(max-width: 659px) 100vw, 659px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Congratulations!</strong> Your website has now been claimed successfully.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article helped you verify your WordPress website with Pinterest. Use this tutorial, and it’ll help drive more referral traffic to your website, boost engagement, and build your brand at rocket speed.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You may also want to check out our post on <a href="https://aioseo.com/how-to-integrate-social-media-into-your-website/">how to integrate social media into your website</a> and <a href="https://aioseo.com/how-to-best-optimize-images-in-wordpress/">how to best optimize your images in WordPress</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not using <a href="https://aioseo.com/pricing/">AIOSEO</a> yet? What are you waiting for?</p>The post <a href="https://aioseo.com/how-to-verify-your-wordpress-website-with-pinterest/">How to Verify Your WordPress Website With Pinterest (Step by Step)</a> first appeared on <a href="https://aioseo.com">AIOSEO</a>.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:76:"https://aioseo.com/how-to-verify-your-wordpress-website-with-pinterest/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"4";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:82:"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:44:"7 Best WordPress Redirect Plugins (Compared)";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:126:"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-redirect-plugins/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=best-wordpress-redirect-plugins";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:60:"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-redirect-plugins/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 14 Jul 2021 12:16:15 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:19:"All in One SEO Pack";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"Redirect plugins for WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"Top Redirect WordPress Plugins";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"WordPress plugins for redirects";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"https://aioseo.com/?p=45921";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:420:"<p>Looking to find the best WordPress redirect plugins for your site? There are various reasons when you need to create a redirect. You want to redirect users to another page because the original page no longer exists. You want to&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href="https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-redirect-plugins/">7 Best WordPress Redirect Plugins (Compared)</a> first appeared on <a href="https://aioseo.com">AIOSEO</a>.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Saud Razzak";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:19177:"<p>Looking to find the best WordPress redirect plugins for your site?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are various reasons when you need to create a redirect.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>You want to redirect users to another page because the original page no longer exists. </li><li>You want to revamp a page and temporarily move your visitors to a different page.</li><li>You’ve changed the post or page URL and want the visitors to see the new URL.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>In simple words, you just need to make sure the visitors don’t leave your site without getting the information they are looking for.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this post, we’ll show you some of the best redirection plugins and help you choose the right plugin for your WordPress website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some quick links to what we’ll cover in this article. If you’re in a hurry, you can jump directly to the section you want to read.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href="#What-Is-a-Redirection-in-WordPress">What Is a Redirection in WordPress?</a></li><li><a href="#Best-WordPress-Redirect-Plugins">Best WordPress Redirect Plugins (2021)</a></li><li><a href="#Best-Redirect-Plugin-for-Your-WordPress-Site">Best Redirect Plugin for Your WordPress Site</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s dig in.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id="What-Is-a-Redirection-in-WordPress">What Is a Redirect in WordPress?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A redirect in WordPress is the best way to tell web browsers that the requested page can be found at a different location.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As a result, the browser automatically loads the page from the new location without impacting the user experience.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are several types of redirects, with the following three being the most common on WordPress websites:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>301 Redirect:</strong> Indicates that the resource has been permanently moved to a new location.</li><li><strong>302 Redirect:</strong> Indicates that the resource has temporarily moved to a new location but the HTTP method can be changed.</li><li><strong>307 Redirect:</strong> Indicates that the resource has temporarily moved to a new location but the HTTP method should remain the same.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>By using WordPress redirect, you can rest assured that your users won&#8217;t see <a href="https://aioseo.com/how-to-easily-find-and-fix-404-errors-in-wordpress/">404 Page Not Found Error</a> and doesn&#8217;t affect search rankings. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Alright! Now you know why you need to use a redirect. Let’s get into the list.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id="Best-WordPress-Redirect-Plugins">Best WordPress Redirect Plugins (2021)</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are the top 7 WordPress redirect plugins that we’re going to check out so that you can pick the best fit for your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. <a href="https://aioseo.com/pricing/">All in One SEO for WordPress (AIOSEO)</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://aioseo.com/pricing/"><img loading="lazy" width="730" height="447" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-2.png" alt="AIOSEO - Best WordPress Redirect Plugins" class="wp-image-45907" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-2.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-2-300x184.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-2-600x367.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-2-98x60.png 98w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-2-147x90.png 147w" sizes="(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://aioseo.com/pricing/"></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://aioseo.com/pricing/">AIOSEO</a> is a popular WordPress SEO plugin that allows you to set up redirections with a single click.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The plugin comes with a simple redirect manager to easily manage all types of redirections without writing a single line of code.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>All you need to do is go to the <strong>WordPress Dashboard » All In One SEO » Redirects</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="620" height="261" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-Redirect-Settings.png" alt="AIOSEO Redirects Settings" class="wp-image-45923" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-Redirect-Settings.png 620w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-Redirect-Settings-300x126.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-Redirect-Settings-600x253.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-Redirect-Settings-143x60.png 143w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-Redirect-Settings-214x90.png 214w" sizes="(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can add any type of redirection by simply adding the URLs and selecting the type of redirection.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Easy peasy!!</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong><strong>:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Import and Export Redirection:</strong> Import and export redirection from other plugins. For more details, check out our guide on <a href="https://aioseo.com/import-and-export-redirects-in-wordpress/">how to easily import and export redirects in WordPress</a>.</li><li><strong>Check Redirect:</strong> AIOSEO’s redirection manager comes with a built-in redirect checker. This allows you to quickly check if your redirects are working properly.</li><li><strong>Automatic Redirects:</strong> You can set the automatic redirects to your posts and pages.</li><li><strong>Logs:</strong> You can check the records of all redirects to see all the useful information.</li><li><strong>Full Site Redirect:</strong> You can easily redirect your entire site in a few clicks. Everything will be redirected except WordPress login and admin.</li><li><strong>Local SEO:</strong> It tells Google about your business, including business name, email address, location, hours, and price range.</li><li><strong>Breadcrumbs Navigation:</strong> This allows you to <a href="https://aioseo.com/docs/displaying-breadcrumbs-on-your-site/">display breadcrumbs</a> exactly the way you want and thus improves the user experience on your website.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>This is not all &#8211; AIOSEO comes with all the essential features to optimize your website for search engines. You can check out the complete <a href="https://aioseo.com/features/">features of AIOSEO</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong><strong>:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO offers <strong>4</strong> different plans. The starting price of this plugin is <strong>$49.50 </strong>per year.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>2. <a href="https://aioseo.com/recommends/yoast-premium/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Yoast SEO</a></h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://aioseo.com/recommends/yoast-premium/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><img loading="lazy" width="611" height="301" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Yoast-SEO-1.png" alt="" class="wp-image-45924" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Yoast-SEO-1.png 611w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Yoast-SEO-1-300x148.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Yoast-SEO-1-600x296.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Yoast-SEO-1-122x60.png 122w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Yoast-SEO-1-183x90.png 183w" sizes="(max-width: 611px) 100vw, 611px" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://yoast.com/wordpress/plugins/seo/"></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://aioseo.com/recommends/yoast-premium/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Yoast</a> is yet another SEO plugin that also lets you easily set up WordPress redirection on your website. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Just as AIOSEO, Yoast also allows you to choose from several different types of redirections with a few clicks. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong><strong>:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Automatic Redirects:</strong> This plugin offers automatic redirects when you move the post and pages of your WordPress websites.</li><li><strong>Manage Redirects:</strong> You can manage your redirects in your site admin, where you can search and filter the list.</li><li><strong>Import and Export Redirect:</strong> You can easily import and export redirects in CSV format.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Aside from redirection management, Yoast also comes bundled with essential SEO features, such as optimize articles for keywords and keyphrases, the ability to write meta tags, structured data blocks, and more. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong><strong>:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The pricing for a <a href="https://aioseo.com/recommends/yoast-premium/">single site license</a> starts at <strong>$89</strong> per year.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>3. <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/redirection/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Redirection</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/redirection/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><img loading="lazy" width="691" height="310" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Redirection-Plugin-WordPress.png" alt="Redirection Plugin WordPress" class="wp-image-46569" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Redirection-Plugin-WordPress.png 691w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Redirection-Plugin-WordPress-300x135.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Redirection-Plugin-WordPress-600x269.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Redirection-Plugin-WordPress-134x60.png 134w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Redirection-Plugin-WordPress-201x90.png 201w" sizes="(max-width: 691px) 100vw, 691px" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/redirection/"></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/redirection/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Redirection</a> is a free WordPress plugin that allows you to manage redirects on your WordPress website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, it allows conditional redirects with dozens of possibilities like server redirect, role capability redirect, page type redirects, IP address redirect, login status redirect, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You don’t need to be a WordPress expert to use this plugin, as it is easy to set up.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong><strong>:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Import and Export:</strong> This plugin supports the import and export of the redirection.</li><li><strong>Migrate Permalinks:</strong> It allows you to migrate old permalinks simply by entering the old permalinks structure.</li><li><strong>Limited Migration: </strong>This plugin offers limited redirect migration from other SEO plugins.</li><li><strong>Complicated UI: </strong>New users might find it challenging to navigate with the UI.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong><strong>:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The plugin is available for free.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>4. <a href="https://aioseo.com/recommends/rank-math/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Rank Math</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://aioseo.com/recommends/rank-math/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><img loading="lazy" width="700" height="301" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/RankMath-1.png" alt="RankMath" class="wp-image-45926" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/RankMath-1.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/RankMath-1-300x129.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/RankMath-1-600x258.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/RankMath-1-140x60.png 140w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/RankMath-1-209x90.png 209w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://rankmath.com/"></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://aioseo.com/recommends/rank-math/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Rank Math</a> is another WordPress SEO plugin that offers the redirect feature. This plugin is very similar to Yoast. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The major drawback of this plugin is it only supports <strong>3</strong> redirect types. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong><strong>:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>404 Error: </strong>It allows you to monitor your site for 404 errors.</li><li><strong>Custom Redirection:</strong> You can set up custom redirects for any page you need.</li><li><strong>Simple and Clean:</strong> Easy setup wizard and simple and clean UI.</li><li><strong>Manage Redirects:</strong> It allows you to easily create, manage, enable, or disable redirects at any scale.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Pricing for a single site license starts at <strong>$59</strong> per year.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>5. <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/https-redirection/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Easy HTTPS Redirection (SSL)</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/https-redirection/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><img loading="lazy" width="658" height="294" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Easy-HTTPS-Redirection.png" alt="Easy HTTPS Redirection" class="wp-image-46582" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Easy-HTTPS-Redirection.png 658w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Easy-HTTPS-Redirection-300x134.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Easy-HTTPS-Redirection-600x268.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Easy-HTTPS-Redirection-134x60.png 134w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Easy-HTTPS-Redirection-201x90.png 201w" sizes="(max-width: 658px) 100vw, 658px" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/https-redirection/"></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/https-redirection/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Easy HTTPS Redirection</a> shows only the HTTPS URLs to the visitors. If the visitors land at a non-HTTPS URL, they will automatically be redirected to the HTTPS URL.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, you can force your full domain to be auto-redirected to the HTTPS version of your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>URL Redirection</strong>: It will automatically redirect your users from HTTP to HTTPS</li><li><strong>Redirect Entire Domain:</strong> Easy HTTPS redirection offers auto-redirect to the entire domain or just a few pages.</li><li><strong>Only Works with SSL: </strong>This plugin only works if the SSL is installed.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The plugin is available for free.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>6. <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/eps-301-redirects/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">301 Redirects – Easy Redirect Manager</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/eps-301-redirects/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><img loading="lazy" width="691" height="295" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/301-redirect-easy-redirect-manager.png" alt="301 redirects - easy redirect manager" class="wp-image-46580" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/301-redirect-easy-redirect-manager.png 691w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/301-redirect-easy-redirect-manager-300x128.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/301-redirect-easy-redirect-manager-600x256.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/301-redirect-easy-redirect-manager-141x60.png 141w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/301-redirect-easy-redirect-manager-211x90.png 211w" sizes="(max-width: 691px) 100vw, 691px" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/eps-301-redirects/"></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/eps-301-redirects/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">301 Redirects</a> is a free WordPress redirect plugin that allows you to create 301 and 302 redirects in simple steps.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This plugin is a good choice for you if you just need a basic redirect plugin that doesn&#8217;t come bundled with other SEO features. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong><strong>:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>404 Error Pages:</strong> You can set a custom destination URL to redirect users from 404 error pages.</li><li><strong>Import and Export:</strong> It allows you to import and export bulk redirections.</li><li><strong>Limited Features:</strong> The features of the plugin are limited.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong><strong>:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The plugin is available for free.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>7. <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/quick-pagepost-redirect-plugin/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Quick Page/Post Redirect Plugin</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/quick-pagepost-redirect-plugin/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><img loading="lazy" width="665" height="295" src="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/quick-post-and-pages-redirection-plugin.png" alt="Quick post and page redirect plugin" class="wp-image-46581" srcset="https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/quick-post-and-pages-redirection-plugin.png 665w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/quick-post-and-pages-redirection-plugin-300x133.png 300w, https://a